        <td bgcolor="ivory" colspan="2" valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/19/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 19:22:43</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=115"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> <as posted on the main LOA website)</P><P>Asheron's Call</P><P>Attack of the Killer Statues!</P><P>After being away from the world of Dereth for almost a week I return to find much changed, some of which is not for the better. I stripped down to my girth (in typical Gharudium fashion) and took a stroll/shopping trip through the streets of ancient Qualabar only to most suddenly and unexpectedly meet a deadly new enemy. As I stood by the jewelers shop greeting fellow shoppers (and doing a trade or two) I feel the crackle of magic in the air. My hair stands on end, indicating to me I have just been cursed with a type of magic vulntrability spell. As I start to turn around I am hit in quick succession by three powerful magical bludgeon attacks and fall on the ground stuned (ok, ok..dead actually!). <BR>Upon waking at my far off lifestone I mutter ad few curses and wonder just what happened. I begin the journey back to Qualabar to retreive my body and perhaps have vengence on whatever vile person/creature it was that slew me. As I portaled out of a magical tunnel into the town of Qualbar I saw in the distance giant "things" lumbering thru the town. These giants were taller then many of the towns buildings and there appeared to be five of them. Getting closer to town I see that the giants are evil manifestations of the towns benificial statue come to life. Our good golem statue still stands like a rock upon its pedestal but exact copies of it had come to life and were rampaging though, and even in, the shops and houses of town. Chaos reigned througout with people fleeing, dead bodies littering the street and arrows, shattered shields other battle debris laying around. A brave group of people were just outside town getting on their armor to charge back into battle. I put on my remaining armor, steeled my nerves and joined up with a group of fighters, archers and mages in an effort to reclaim the town. Small groups of townsfolks were fighting the statues all over town and one had even already been killed. Thankfully the evil creatures didn't seem to be able to work in a group and coordinate their attack so one by one we were able to overcome them. </P><P>After the last monster was slain their was much rejoicing, congraduating, back slapping and sighs of releif. Once the adrenaline wore off we all collected our belonging off our corpses and then went to the local pub for a pint of cheer. Ahhh, the stories we told. </P><P>A typical day in Dereth? Join us and find out. ;-)</P><P><BR></font></td>

      </tr>

